1.Which of these is a managed compute platform that lets you run stateless containers through web requests or Pub/Sub events?

    Cloud Functions

    App Engine

    Google Kubernetes Engine

Ans.Cloud Run
2.Which of these is a lightweight, fully managed serverless execution environment for building and connecting cloud services?

Ans.Cloud Functions

    App Engine

    Google Kubernetes Engine

    Compute Engine
3.Which of these is a managed environment for deploying containerized apps?

    Cloud Functions

    App Engine

Ans.Google Kubernetes Engine

    Cloud Run
4.What is the Compute Engine feature that allows VMs to be added to or subtracted from an application based on load metrics?

    Load balancing

Ans.Autoscaling

    Persistent disks

    Network time protocol (NTP)
5.Which compute service would be considered IaaS?

    Google Kubernetes Engine

    Cloud Functions

    App Engine

Ans.Compute Engine

6.Which App Engine environment is based on preconfigured container instances?

    Both standard and flexible environments

    Flexible environment

Ans.Standard environment
